\textbf{Answer:} First, we will determine how much money Louis received from each source. We know that the least perfect square is $0$, so all of the perfect squares less than $100$ are $0$, $1$, $4$, $9$, $16$, $25$, $36$, $49$, $64$, and $81$. Of these, $81$ is the greatest, and the only one between $40$ and $50$ is $49$. Therefore, Louis received $81$ dollars from his parents and $49$ dollars from his grandparents. The amount of money that Louis received from his aunt can be expressed as $5^2-5=25-5=20$ dollars. Thus, we can add these amounts to find the total amount of money Louis received. We get\begin{align*}81+20+49&=81+49+20 \\ &=130+20 \\ &=\boxed{150}\text{ dollars}.\end{align*}
